    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4627" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἰαίνω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ι&lt;&gt;ηνα</span>, pass. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ι&lt;&gt;άνθη</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ῖ</span> when with augment): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">warm, soften</span> by
          warming, <i><span class="en">Od. 12.175</span></i>; met.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">warm, melt, move</span> the heart to compassion, cheer,
          etc., <i><span class="en">Od. 15.379</span></i>; often thus in
          pass., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμός, κῆρ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 23.598</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 22.59</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> μέτωπον ἰάνθη</span>,
          ‘brightened,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 15.103</span></i>; also w.
          acc. of specification, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">θῡμόν, φρένας, ψ
            47</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 24.382</span></i>; w. dat.,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 19.537</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
